  title `Short title. Extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765&sectionId=34825&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Destruction of Records Act, 1917.`
  line
  line `^1[It extends to the whole of India except ^2[the territories which, immediately before the`
  line `1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States].]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section1 of Central Act V of 1917.--In section 1 of the principal Act,`
  line `after the expression “except the territories Which immediately before the 1st November 1956`
  line `were comprised in Part ‘B’ States”, the expression “other than the territories specified in`
  line `clause (a) and clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 7 of the States Reorganisation Act,`
  line `1956 (Central Act 37 of 1956)” shall be added.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 3 of 1963, s. 3].`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 3) 1956, for "Part B States ".`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34826)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Definitions.] Rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765&sectionId=34826&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34827)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to certain authorities to make rules for disposal of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765&sectionId=34827&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^13. Power to certain authorities to make rules for disposal of documents.--(1) The`
  line `authorities hereinafter specified may, from time to time, make rules for the disposal, by`
  line `destruction or otherwise, of such documents as ar e, in the opinion of the authority making the`
  line `rules, not of sufficient public value to justify their preservation .`
  line
  line `(2) The authorities shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of documents in the possession or custody of a High Court or of the`
  line `Courts of civil or criminal jurisdiction subordinate thereto,--the High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of documents in the possession or custody of Revenue Courts and`
  line `officers,--the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority^5`
  line `; and`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of documents in the possession or custo dy of any other public`
  line officer,--
  line
  line `^6[(i) if the documents relate to purposes of a State, the State Government or any`
  line `officer specially authorized in that behalf by tha t Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, the Central Government or an officer specially authorized in that behalf`
  line `by that Government.]`
  line
  line `^7[(3) Rules made under this section by any High Court or by a Chief Controlling`
  line `Revenue-authority or by an officer specially authorized in that behalf by any State`
  line `Government shall be subject to the previous approval of the State Government; and rules`
  line `made by an officer specially authorized in that behalf by the Central Government shall be`
  line `subject to the previous approval of the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 3 has been amended in its application to the U.P. by the U.P. Board of Revenue Act, 1922 (U.P.`
  line `12 of 1922), s. 2 and Sch.`
  line
  line `2. For definition of Chief Controlling Revenue -authority, see the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897),`
  line `s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for the L.G., or any officer specially authorized in that behalf by the L.G. ".`
  line
  line `4. Subs., ibid., for sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34828)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Validation of former rules for disposal of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765&sectionId=34828&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `All rules and orders`
  line `directing or authorising the destruction or other disposal of documents in the possession or`
  line `custody of any public officer, heretofore made by a State Government, or with the approval`
  line `of the State Government by any authority not empowered to make such rules under the`
  line `Destruction of Records Act, 1879 (3 of 1879), shall be deemed to have had the force of law`
  line `from the date on which they were made, and all such rules and orders now in force shall`
  line `continue to have the force of law until they are superseded by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34829)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Saving of certain documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765&sectionId=34829&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00015_191705_1523342690765
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to authorise the`
  line `destruction of any document which, under the provisions of any law for the time being in force,`
  line `is to be kept and maintained.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
